cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with Fine-Grained Visual Classification (FGVC), which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a regularization technique based on pairwise confusion energy, which is a common technique in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses a CNN model and attention mechanisms, which are common in multimedia analysis and processing, so it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
